We LOVE Superfine. We had THE BEST food on Saturday #81818 at our wedding lunch at Superfine. Sometimes when you go to a restaurant and you have a large party, the staff starts slacking because they know that gratuity is built in. Y'all, we had a party of 35+ people and their staff was AMAZING. They were SO nice, SO accommodating, just really SO pleasant we want to go host events there more. Everything came out in a timely fashion, they were SUPER patient even though we ended up having a few more people than we expected. It was refreshing to go to a restaurant that has delicious food and a great staff. The menu changes daily based on what farm-to-table ingredients they get. We went back this year for our anniversary brunch. Anytime we can, we recommended Superfine to our friends. Do yourself a favor: Skip the pretention of most of the new Dumbo restaurants and get yourself a delicious and filling meal with a fun crowd. You will NOT be disappointed.

Last Sunday I went all the way there for the third time since I had very good experiences for the first two times. However this time when I got there, I saw several waitresses at the cashier counter, yet nobody seemed to be walking to me and get me seated.So I walked to the counter, one of the waitresses asked me to wait for the African American waitress lady who was figuring out some bills at the counter to get me a seat. I waited for like 3 min but she was still doing those bills, and nobody seated me. I was a bit upset so I sit myself. Another two min went by and this African American lady finally came, however looking somehow unpleased. She asked me why I sit myself, I said because the other lady asked me to wait for you but you were busy and nobody got me seated so I decided to sit myself. Then she looked very unhappy upon hearing what I said and then just walked away, leaving me there in confusion.  When she swung by again I waved to her, she walked over to me with a lot of attitude and she goes 'I am not the waitress and I'll get you one okay?' Then she left again. By that time I was already very upset about their service. Another 1 or 2 min left the African American lady came again, reluctantly pulling out the menu, obviously she is exactly the waitress herself! She just didn't want to take my order just now and gave me so much attitude! I finally ordered the omelette as I did for the first two times, however this time when the food came, the portion turned out to be way much smaller than before, and the omelette was pretty dry. I felt frustrated about the overall experience this time, maybe both the chef and that waitress lady were in bad mood.

I’ve never been here before but searched online and came across here. Called in a to go order and was expecting lunch, but they had brunch so I went for that. I chose the fish tacos and chicken enchiladas. It was very good! I enjoyed the pairings they did with the brunch combo, the fish with the mixed greens was good, came with two lime slices which was great. The salad was appropriately and dressed with some sort of oil & vinaigrette mixture, it wasn’t drippy or gooey and the greens were nice and crispy! The portion size was nice and full, it was good but lacking a kick of flavor, additionally the tortilla wrap was a bit soggy and soft, I would’ve preferred it be crispier or be able to withstand the sauce from the beans and tomato sauce it’s topped with and sitting in. As well as a side of sour cream or guacamole would’ve been a good side.  When I went to pick up my order, the location was nice and clean, spacious, dimly lit (so its great for groups, dates, family, friends, dinner party, brunch), lots of tables, a bar, a stage (which had live music performance going on), and bathrooms that are upkept. Customer service was average, but at end of transaction employee informed me about hours, and I was happy to find out that they are open almost near 24 hours! I believe they close only from 2am-6am if I am recalling correctly. This is great bc in New York it is hard to find places open and serving food, with spacious seating, nice menu selection that anyone might be able to enjoy, and pretty decent parking available.  In a quiet area so you get that cobble stone, warehouse district vibe with that New York feel but less busy with traffic &’pedestrians. Great for New Yorkers and out of Towners bc although it’s on a quiet street, just a few streets up are highways and bridges that can take you out of state, out of town, or into the city! Or if coming back from a night out in the city and grabbing some food to eat in or go, this spot would be ideal. I wouldn’t describe it as a diner or a place that open long hours with bad food,  I think the food quality, seating, location, and space make it a trendy place you can stop by at anytime and would most likely be pleased.  Lastly, I wasn’t sure what the music setting was there. Although it was live music when I went in, it didn’t seem like the musicians were playing covers or singing songs I was familiar with. Which is no problem but I wouldn’t be confident to know what type of music they play through the day, I appreciate performers and days/nights dedicated to them but I wouldn’t want to go there to eat and sit all the time if music I’m not familiarized with. Otherwise and overall, a good experience and reasonable prices, and what seems like lunch specials and deals for each course of the day (breakfast, brunch, dinn).  In conclusion, I would recommend to go here and would go back again!

Service is terrible food was okay.  When we first walked into the restaurant we were very happy because the ambiance had potential. We loved the decor, the space was interesting and there were live musicians; However, as we approached the host we were told that there were reservations and we had an hour and a half.  We didn’t like that but because of our impression of the place we thought it was worth it.  After sitting there for quite a while we saw no sign of a waiter.  When she finally arrived she apologized for her lateness but then after taking our order she dissapeared.  In such a big place there were no signs of waiters/waitresses.  After waiting another long while and wondering about the tea we ordered, and no way to signal her, we asked the host who didn’t seem happy. She responded by saying:  “O.k. I’ll find out.”   A while later she  passed our table and dropped tea bags on her way to her post.  Forty minutes into the meal the host unceremoniously cleared our table   We asked her for the check.  She signaled the waitress for what we assumed was  the check and when she kneeled behind to chat with a couple we thought she would check with us but she didn’t even look.  Needless to say we never got water for the tea.  We were very disappointed.

We came in for brunch on a Sunday and ordered the huevos rancheros and breakfast burrito. Both came to our table swamped in a puddle of water with chilies that the waiter explained was their signature chili sauce. It was inedible. The tortillas were disintegrating in the so called “sauce.” We offered to pay for the drinks we had but the extremely rude manager - a woman who was eating the same huevos rancheros at a table nearby- glanced us up and down and scoffed that she didn’t want our money. Worst dining experience I’ve ever had. Don’t blame your guests for not wanting to eat inedible food. It was like a child doused a good meal with a water balloon. The only pro is that there are plenty of great food options nearby. We found a brunch spot that sympathized with our experience. “We get a few of you each weekend” they laughed.

I have mixed feelings about this restaurant. We were seated pretty fast but for a restaurant that was only half full, they were out of menus to hand out. The staff seemed nice when they addressed us, however, it literally took 20 minutes for someone to take our order. The waitress was apologetic when she finally did come to us. She thought someone else had taken our order. Three people in our group ordered the house salad. It was literally a plate full of lettuce. No tomato. No cucumber.  No onion. Nothing. Just lettuce. For EIGHT DOLLARS! Yep, that's right, eight dollars for a plate of lettuce. Biggest RIP off I've ever seen. The rest of our food was good but I will say one in our party paid $50 for her food and left hungry.

Was in Dumbo this weekend and was looking for a fun friendly place to eat. I found this place on yelp. I entered and waited 5 mins to be acknowledged by the hostess at the top of the ramp. After 5 minutes I politely said "excuse me" to the lady at the hostess table. She replied "I'm doing something, I can't help you". I was so taken aback by how immensely rude and disrespectful she was. I was shocked and my only thought was that she did not want to serve me as an African American woman! There was nothing else that she knew about me that would make her respond to me in such a disgusting manner. I had no choice but to turn around and leave the establishment. So sad that we still encounter these type of people in Our own neighborhoods in 2018. I would never spend any money in a business that employs racists and does not treat all customers with dignity and respect.
